Item Sniping ETL Pipeline Build Plan


-- Each file written should be testable as soon as it is written
-- bottom up (begin with data contracts, -> orchestrator). 

Pure logic first, I/O boundaries, then middleware/glue last
------------------------
1. models.py

Deps: nothing
Every module imports from here

contracts between pipeline stages: 


-RawListing -NormalizedListing -ValuationResult -ScoredListing -ConditionGrade, ListingSource
.........

use Pydantic data classes 


... you need to know what a NormalizedListing looks like before writing an normalizer
Test: instantiate  models, confirm validate catches 
---------------------
2. config.py

Deps (stdlib tomllib)

every module accepts config dict

defines shape of config  --> downstream modules can reference them


Testing: load with and without a file, verify defaults work correctly
------------------------------

3. normalizer.py

deps: models.py

core signal extraction - central logic in the system, most tunable. No I/O. Fast to iterate on. 

Bulk of tests live in models.py

-------------------

4. valuator.py

deps models.py

take's normalized output and produces cost estimate. 


You can't write this before normalizer because the features aren't defined yet for the (item) e.g. camera (is_body_only, bundle_contents, condition) to know
"why do i adjust for).

Testing: feed normalized listings with known features. Assert dollar amount and adjust breakdowns


------

5. scorer.py

deps model.py

Consumes: both: NormalizedListing and ValuationResult

scoring components (magnitude, confidence, risk) 

test: verify score math, 
alert threshold, 





--------------




6. collectors/base.py


deps models.py

abstract interface: connect() -> list[RawListing] 


------------

7. collectors/mock.py


deps base.py mock.py


lets the full system run without waiting for ebay API approval

Six fixtures cover the patterns the normalizer needs:


1) Clean body only
2) Bundle
3) For parts
4) Vague Listing
5) Mega Bundle
6) Typical used listing

test: call_collect()

verify to return RawListings

